title: Asia shares touch new 19-month highs ahead of U.S.-China trade deal
text: Asian shares rose to new 19-month highs on Monday ahead of the expected signing on a Phase 1 China-U.S. trade deal, although markets have yet to see the details of the agreement.

title: JPMorgan health-care expert: This is the 'year of the consumer' at 2020 health-care conference
text: JPMorgan Managing Director Lisa Gill previewed the 38th Annual J.P. Morgan Healthcare Conference that will be centered around the consumer and disruptors.

title: Another Bank of England policy-maker says he's open to rate cut: report
text: A key Bank of England policy-maker has said he may vote to cut interest rates later this month if the economy does not show improvement.

title: Oil dips on easing U.S.-Iran tensions, eyes on China trade deal
text: Oil prices edged down on Monday as fears of conflict between the United States and Iran eased, although the decline was checked by the planned signing of an initial U.S.-China trade deal this week, which could boost demand.

title: Asia shares flatline, wait for U.S. and China to seal trade deal
text: Asian shares paused near 19-month peaks on Monday ahead of the expected signing on a Sino-U.S. trade deal, though talks on a phase two package are likely to drag on for months.

title: China's U.S. trade deal commitments not changed in translation: Mnuchin
text: China's commitments in the Phase 1 trade deal with the United States were not changed during a lengthy translation process and will be released this week as the document is signed in Washington, U.S. Treasury Secretary Steven Mnuchin said on Sunday.

title: Pressure for 2020 as U.S. companies report end of weak profit year
text: As major U.S. corporations prepare to close the books on a lackluster year of profit growth, they may need to shore up confidence that 2020 will show significant improvement to keep the stock market's rally going.
